53232|accessdate=January 22, 2017|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=December 9, 2016}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"FastCompanyInnovative2017\">{{cite news|title=Why Illumination Entertainment Is One Of The Most Innovative Companies Of 2017|url=https://www.fastcompany.com/3067473/why-illumination-entertainment-is-one-of-the-most-innovative-compa|accessdate=February 11, 2017|work=Fast Company|date=February 13, 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.illumination.com/}}\n* [https://www.illuminationmacguff.com/ Illumination Mac Guff official website]\n* {{imdb company|id=0221986}}\n* {{bcdb |Other_Studios/I/Illumination_Entertainment/|Illumination Entertainment}}\n\n{{Illumination Entertainment}}\n{{NBCUniversal}}\n{{Film Studio}}\n{{Animation industry in the United States}}\n\n[[Category:American animation studios]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Santa Monica, California]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 2007]]\n[[Category:Illumination Entertainment| ]]\n[[Category:Universal Pictures]]\n[[Category:2007 establishments in California]]\n[[Category:Film production companies of the United States]]\n", "name_user": "73.13.163.64", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eUpcoming films)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illumination_(company)"}
{"title_page": "Sinclair Ferguson", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2017}}\n{{infobox theologian\n|name=Sinclair Ferguson\n|image = \n|era = 20th and 21st century\n|birth_date = {{birth year and age|1948}}\n|birth_place = \n|death_date = \n|occupation = Professor, Author, Public Speaker\n|tradition_movement = [[Reformed]]\n|notable_works = ''Reformed Confessions Harmonized''<br/>\n''In Christ Alone: Living the Gospel Centered Life''<br/>\n''The Christian Life: A Doctrinal Introduction''\n}}\n\n'''Sinclair Buchanan Ferguson''' (born 1948) is a Scottish [[Theology|theologian]] known in [[Reformed churches|Reformed Christian]] circles for his teaching, writing, and editorial work. He is Chancellor's Professor of Systematic Theology at Reformed Theological Seminary since 2017,<ref>https://www.rts.edu/seminary/newsevents/NewsDetails.aspx?id=2537</ref> commuting from [[Scotland]] where he is an assistant minister at St. Peter's [[Free Church of Scotland (post 1900)|Free Church of Scotland]], [[Dundee]].\n\n==Career==\nFerguson studied at the [[University of Aberdeen]] for all of his university education, firstly a master or arts, then a bachelor of divinity, before gaining his received his [[Ph.D.]] During his days as a student, he worshipped at Gilcomstons South Church, under the ministry of William Still.<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Reading and Preaching of the Scriptures in the Worship of the Christian Church, Vol. 7: Our Own Time|last=Old|first=Hughes Oliphant|publisher=Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing|year=2010|isbn=|location=|pages=135-136}}</ref>\n\nFerguson was ordained as a minister in the [[Church of Scotland]] in 1971, becoming a minister in the most northerly parish in Scotland, becoming the minister of St. John's, Baltasound on the island of [[Unst]], Shetland.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rts.edu/people/dr-sinclair-b-ferguson/|title=Dr. Sinclair B. Ferguson|website=Reformed Theological Seminary|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref> He was the pastor there for 10 years. After this decade on Unst, he was offered a teaching position as a part-time Professor of [[systematic theology|Systematic Theology]] at [[Westminster Theological Seminary]], Philadelphia.\n\nHe then moved back to his native Scotland in 1997, filling the pulpit at [[St George's-Tron Church]], [[Glasgow]], succeeding the successful 20 year ministry of Eric Alexander. \n\nIn the mid-2000s, he then transferred back to the US to the [[Associate Reformed Presbyterian Church]], serving as the senior pastor of historic [[First Presbyterian Church (Columbia, South Carolina)|First Presbyterian Church of Columbia, South Carolina]]. \n\nFrom 25 August 2013, he has served as a preacher and elder at St. Peter's Free Church, Dundee.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theaquilareport.com/sinclair-ferguson-to-join-st-peters-free-church-in-dundee/|title=Sinclair Ferguson to Join St Peter\u2019s Free Church in Dundee|date=2013-07-19|website=The Aquila Report|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref> \n\n=== Other Roles ===\nHe has served as an editor with the [[Banner of Truth Trust]].\n\nHe was also a professor of systematic theology at [[Redeemer Seminary]] in Dallas.\n\nHe has held the Charles Krahe Chair for [[systematic theology|Systematic Theology]] at Westminster Theological Seminary.\n\nHe also previously served as a council member of the [[Alliance of Confessing Evangelicals]].\n\n==Works==\nFerguson speaks at numerous conferences worldwide. Books he has written, edited or contributed to include:\n*''The Whole Christ: Legalism, Antinomianism, & Gospel Assurance--Why the Marrow Controversy Still Matters'' (2016) {{ISBN|978-1433548000}}\n*''The Christian Life: A Doctrinal Introduction'' (2013)  {{ISBN|978-1848712591}}\n*''Name above All Names'' (2013) with [[Alistair Begg]] {{ISBN|978-1433537752}}\n*''Deserted by God'' (2013) {{ISBN|978-1848711532}}\n*''The Grace of Repentance (Redesign) (Today's Issues)'' (2011) {{ISBN|978-1433519833}}\n*''By Grace Alone: How the Grace of God Amazes me'' (2010) {{ISBN|978-1567692020}}\n* ''In Christ Alone: Living the Gospel Centered Life'' (2007)\n* ''John Owen: The Man and His Theology'' (2003) {{ISBN|0-87552-674-8}}, contributor about [[John Owen (theologian)|John Owen]]\n* ''The Preacher's Commentary - Vol. 21 - Daniel'' (2002) {{ISBN|0-7852-4795-5}}\n* ''The Big Book of Questions & Answers about Jesus'' (2000) {{ISBN|1-85792-559-9}}\n* ''The Grace of Repentance (Today's Issues)'' (2000) {{ISBN|1-58134-165-2}}\n* ''Reformed Confessions Harmonized'' (1999) {{ISBN|0-8010-5222-X}}, editor with [[Joel Beeke]]\n* ''Let's Study Mark'' (1999) {{ISBN|0-85151-755-2}}\n* ''Let's Study Philippians'' (1998) {{ISBN|0-85151-714-5}}\n* ''Let's Study Ephesians'' (2005) {{ISBN|0-85151-907-5}}\n* ''Big Book of Questions and Answers'' (1997) {{ISBN|1-85792-295-6}}\n* ''The Holy Spirit'' (1997) {{ISBN|0-8308-1536-8}}\n* ''Heart for God'' (1996) {{ISBN|0-85151-502-9}}\n* ''The Christian Life'' (1996) {{ISBN|0-85151-516-9}}\n* ''Discovering God's Will'' (1996) {{ISBN|0-85151-334-4}}\n* ''Sermon on the Mount'' (1996) {{ISBN|0-85151-519-3}}\n* ''The Pundit's Folly'' (1996) {{ISBN|0-85151-676-9}}\n* ''Grow in Grace'' (1989) {{ISBN|0-85151-557-6}}\n* ''Children of the Living God'' (1989) {{ISBN|0-85151-536-3}}\n* ''New Dictionary of Theology (Master Reference Collection)'' (1988) {{ISBN|0-8308-1400-0}}, editor with [[David Wright (theologian)|David Wright]] and [[J. I. Packer]]\n* ''Daniel (Mastering the Old Testament, Vol 19)'' (1988) {{ISBN|0-8499-3557-1}}\n* ''John Owen on the Christian Life'' (1987) {{ISBN|0-85151-503-7}}\n* ''Kingdom Life in a Fallen World'' ''- Living Out the Sermon on the Mount'' (1986) {{ISBN|0-89109-194-7}}\n* ''Know Your Christian Life'' (1981) {{ISBN|0-87784-371-6}}\n* ''Faithful God - An exposition of the book of Ruth'' (2005) {{ISBN|978-1-85049-216-0}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*The Tron Church, Glasgow formerly St George's-Tron Church\n*Redeemer Seminary\n*[http://www.alliancenet.org/ Alliance of Confessing Evangelicals]\n*[http://www.firstprescolumbia.org/ First Presbyterian Church - Columbia, SC]\n*[http://www.stpeters-dundee.org.uk/ St. Peter's Free Church, Dundee]\n*[https://www.monergism.com/thethreshold/articles/bio/ferguson.html Biographical Sketch]\n*[https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/the-westminster-standards/id533896327?mt=2 Lectures on the Westminster Standards]\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ferguson, Sinclair}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Scottish Calvinist and Reformed theologians]]\n[[Category:Westminster Theological Seminary faculty]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Aberdeen]]\n[[Category:Ministers of the Church of Scotland]]\n[[Category:Ministers of the Free Church of Scotland]]\n[[Category:20th-century Calvinist and Reformed theologians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Calvinist and Reformed theologians]]\n[[Category:Scottish evangelicals]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2017}}\n{{infobox theologian\n|name=Sinclair Ferguson\n|image = \n|era = 20th and 21st century\n|birth_date = {{birth year and age|1948}}\n|birth_place = \n|death_date = \n|occupation = Professor, Author, Public Speaker\n|tradition_movement = [[Reformed]]\n|notable_works = ''Reformed Confessions Harmonized''<br/>\n''In Christ Alone: Living the Gospel Centered Life''<br/>\n''The Christian Life: A Doctrinal Introduction''\n}}\n\n'''Sinclair Buchanan Ferguson''' (born 1948) is a Scottish [[Theology|theologian]] known in [[Reformed churches|Reformed Christian]] circles for his teaching, writing, and editorial work. He is Chancellor's Professor of Systematic Theology at Reformed Theological Seminary since 2017,<ref>https://www.rts.edu/seminary/newsevents/NewsDetails.aspx?id=2537</ref> commuting from [[Scotland]] where he is an assistant minister at St. Peter's [[Free Church of Scotland (post 1900)|Free Church of Scotland]], [[Dundee]].\n\n==Career==\nFerguson studied at the [[University of Aberdeen]] for all of his university education, firstly a master or arts, then a bachelor of divinity, before gaining his received his [[Ph.D.]] During his days as a student, he worshipped at Gilcomstons South Church, under the ministry of William Still.<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Reading and Preaching of the Scriptures in the Worship of the Christian Church, Vol. 7: Our Own Time|last=Old|first=Hughes Oliphant|publisher=Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing|year=2010|isbn=|location=|pages=135-136}}</ref>\n\nFerguson was ordained as a minister in the [[Church of Scotland]] in 1971, becoming a minister in the most northerly parish in Scotland, becoming the minister of St. John's, Baltasound on the island of [[Unst]], Shetland.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rts.edu/people/dr-sinclair-b-ferguson/|title=Dr. Sinclair B. Ferguson|website=Reformed Theological Seminary|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref> He was the pastor there for 10 years. After this decade on Unst, he was offered a teaching position as a part-time Professor of [[systematic theology|Systematic Theology]] at [[Westminster Theological Seminary]], Philadelphia.\n\nHe then moved back to his native Scotland in 1997, filling the pulpit at [[St George's-Tron Church]], [[Glasgow]], succeeding the successful 20 year ministry of Eric Alexander. \n\nIn the mid-2000's, he then transferred back to the US to the [[Associate Reformed Presbyterian Church]], serving as the senior pastor of historic [[First Presbyterian Church (Columbia, South Carolina)|First Presbyterian Church of Columbia, South Carolina]]. \n\nFrom 25 August 2013, he has served as a preacher and elder at St. Peter's Free Church, Dundee.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theaquilareport.com/sinclair-ferguson-to-join-st-peters-free-church-in-dundee/|title=Sinclair Ferguson to Join St Peter\u2019s Free Church in Dundee|date=2013-07-19|website=The Aquila Report|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref> \n\n=== Other Roles ===\nHe has served as an editor with the [[Banner of Truth Trust]].\n\nHe was also a professor of systematic theology at [[Redeemer Seminary]] in Dallas.\n\nHe has held the Charles Krahe Chair for [[systematic theology|Systematic Theology]] at Westminster Theological Seminary.\n\nHe also previously served as a council member of the [[Alliance of Confessing Evangelicals]].\n\n==Works==\nFerguson speaks at numerous conferences worldwide. Books he has written, edited or contributed to include:\n*''The Whole Christ: Legalism, Antinomianism, & Gospel Assurance--Why the Marrow Controversy Still Matters'' (2016) {{ISBN|978-1433548000}}\n*''The Christian Life: A Doctrinal Introduction'' (2013)  {{ISBN|978-1848712591}}\n*''Name above All Names'' (2013) with [[Alistair Begg]] {{ISBN|978-1433537752}}\n*''Deserted by God'' (2013) {{ISBN|978-1848711532}}\n*''The Grace of Repentance (Redesign) (Today's Issues)'' (2011) {{ISBN|978-1433519833}}\n*''By Grace Alone: How the Grace of God Amazes me'' (2010) {{ISBN|978-1567692020}}\n* ''In Christ Alone: Living the Gospel Centered Life'' (2007)\n* ''John Owen: The Man and His Theology'' (2003) {{ISBN|0-87552-674-8}}, contributor about [[John Owen (theologian)|John Owen]]\n* ''The Preacher's Commentary - Vol. 21 - Daniel'' (2002) {{ISBN|0-7852-4795-5}}\n* ''The Big Book of Questions & Answers about Jesus'' (2000) {{ISBN|1-85792-559-9}}\n* ''The Grace of Repentance (Today's Issues)'' (2000) {{ISBN|1-58134-165-2}}\n* ''Reformed Confessions Harmonized'' (1999) {{ISBN|0-8010-5222-X}}, editor with [[Joel Beeke]]\n* ''Let's Study Mark'' (1999) {{ISBN|0-85151-755-2}}\n* ''Let's Study Philippians'' (1998) {{ISBN|0-85151-714-5}}\n* ''Let's Study Ephesians'' (2005) {{ISBN|0-85151-907-5}}\n* ''Big Book of Questions and Answers'' (1997) {{ISBN|1-85792-295-6}}\n* ''The Holy Spirit'' (1997) {{ISBN|0-8308-1536-8}}\n* ''Heart for God'' (1996) {{ISBN|0-85151-502-9}}\n* ''The Christian Life'' 